#11982 Would be adding support for commit templating utilities a good idea?
opened by Milo123459 in
desktop/desktop
Thanks for the fast response! Thanks for the kind words about glitter. Glitter is something you install via a binary, so it just has to be available in the $PATH, something like scoop or homebrew can do this. I envision this, glitter has a thing called type_enums, ensuring an argument is one of the values specified in the type enums. When you get onto an argument with a type_enum, a drop-down appears which has all valid type_enums and you can click to insert it. A command coming in the next version called `glitter template ...` will template out the arguments allowing for construction of the commit message. I also planned on adding some sort of lock onto the commit button if not all terms are met, ie, there is an invalid type_enum or something or not enough arguments.
Thanks!
